name: the128
description:
let me put it this way: think of a country that has sold it's own lands in the names of reputation and dignity. and as if that wasn't enough, think of that country stealing 128 billion dollars from it's central bank.

those two men with the bags represents the people of that country. and the man lying dead on the floor represents government.

that poster means ''where's the 128 billion dollars'' in turkish.
